The government approved, on Wednesday, the "National Strategy on Immigration for the period 2015-2018" and "The Action Plan for the current year", documents considered to be "another stage that Romania is going through as part of efforts to modernize the process of managing immigration on the national territory", according to a press release.
The strategy aims to effectively manage the phenomenon of immigration, including general strategic objectives, specific objectives and action guidelines that reflect the policies established at European level, adapted to national realities.
In view of the problems faced by the states in the immediate vicinity of Romania, measures for the unitary and coherent management of situations caused by the possible emergence of an influx of illegal immigrants on the territory of Romania, generated by situations of political, social, economic or military crisis.
