On the other hand, the document also sets out some general strategic objectives related to immigration, such as: promoting legal migration, stricter controls of the legality of the residence of third-country nationals on the territory of Romania and the appropriate application of the measures of removal and restrictive measures of the national system.
The national strategy also includes specific objectives relevant to the implementation and implementation of the overall strategic objectives.
Among them are: the ease of access on the territory of Romania of third-country nationals who meet the needs of employment, the promotion of access of third-country nationals to higher education institutions in Romania for the areas and professions identified as deficit.
